# Dispatch scope (supersedes operations user id)

**On-demand rule.** Mission Control warm-up loads [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/bootstrap.mdc`](bootstrap.mdc) as the sole R&D `alwaysApply: true` bootstrap. Read **this file** when you need dispatch-scoped operations paths or phase-tagged storage contracts — not on every dispatch warm-up.

Normative hosting layout: [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/0_hosting-repo.mdc) § **Operations storage phases**, § **Dispatch bundles under `operations/`**, and § **Plans (dispatch-scoped discovery)**.

---

## Agent dispatch scope (binding)

Every Mission Control agent lane on a dispatch is bound to **one dispatch scope**:

| Field | Source | Agent use |
|-------|--------|-----------|
| **`dispatchId`** | Warm-up / spawn preamble (**Active dispatch UUID**) | Stable dispatch identity; never infer from epoch folder name alone |
| **Bundle directory** | Warm-up / spawn preamble (absolute path) | Read/write dispatch bundle artifacts **only** under this directory |
| **Slot id** | Lane identity block | Open **only** `dispatch-lane.<slotId>.v1.json` for this lane unless spawn handover names another lane file in the **same** bundle |

**Forbidden:**

- Constructing `.sedea/operations/.../` or `.sedea/operations/joint/...` paths for lane work
- Cross-reading **`parent-child-registry.v1.json`**, **`dispatch-tab.v1.json`**, or ship-ledger from **other** dispatch bundle folders
- **`ls -lt`** (or any mtime sort) across all dispatch folders under `.sedea/operations/`
- Inferring dispatch scope from “newest” folder, parallel tabs, or PR index alone without **`targetPlanSlug`** + active **`dispatchId`**

Refresh host identity with MCP **`sedea_get_current_user`** when a skill requires it — **not** to derive operations filesystem paths.

