## Phase-tagged storage (hybrid migration)

Operations persistence is migrating from filesystem bundles to workspace-bound RxDB/SQLite. Follow the **active phase** in Sedea rule **0** — do not mix legacy and new contracts on the same turn.

| Phase | Agent contract |
|-------|----------------|
| **Phase 0 — governance** | Filesystem bundles; scope = **`dispatchId`** + **bundle directory** + explicit plan paths from spawn **`inputs`** |
| **Hybrid** | DB-first for covered dispatch entities; filesystem fallback when entity not in workspace DB (host logs fallback — agents do not open raw DB URLs) |
| **DB-only** | Dispatch CRUD via workspace DB; no epoch-folder discovery |

During **Phase 0** and **hybrid**, the host may still resolve internal filesystem paths. That resolution is **host-internal** — agents must not document or rely on **user-id** path segments.

---

## Plans and docs paths

| Surface | Rule |
|---------|------|
| **PR / phase plans** | Use **`targetPlanPath`**, **`parentPlanPath`**, or other explicit spawn **`inputs`** — absolute or workspace-relative paths supplied by Mission Control |
| **Follow-up edits** | Reuse the anchored absolute plan path from the lane — do not re-derive from directory segments under `.sedea/operations/` |
| **Docs reports** | Write only when a skill names the doc type; path comes from Mission Control handover or skill procedure on the **main hosting clone** |

**Path placeholders in documentation:** `` `...` `` inside path examples marks **omitted middle segments**, not a folder named `...`. Substitute the **bundle-relative** or **handover-supplied** segment — never literal **`joint`** or a user-id segment you constructed yourself.

